This map is one where you spawn, press the blue button, wait 10 secs, then the door opens, making both teams in view, so be sure to hide behind one of the many obstacles! Then this is where the killing starts! =) The door closes after 15 secs, giving time to reload and find a new hiding place, then opens again 5 secs later, then closes after another 15 secs. The button must be pressed again to open it again after 2 opens.

There is a hidden platform in both spawns and a hidden button in both spawns which can enable a huge bomb to go off. If you hear: "The bomb has been planted!" then you know someone has started the timer for 60 secs. Just before the 60 secs are up, you will hear: "Get out of there, it's gonna blow!" then after the 60 secs... *BOOM* (You wont need any extra sounds to download for this to work, just the map.)

**NOTE: THIS MAP IS NOT RECOMMENDED FOR USE WITH PLUGINS WHICH GIVE WEAPONS AND/OR ALLOW RESPAWNING. FOR MOST ENJOYMENT, USE ON A NORMAL SERVER. BOTS DO NOT BEHAVE VERY WELL AND THEY CAN CAUSE MAJOR FPS LAG; THEY ARE NOT RECOMMENDED.**

It is recommended that there is at least 6 people per team on this map for maximum enjoyment.

A fun little fy map that has working carts that move from bunker to bunker, and lots of cover from the broken down city and working cannons.

This map was originally named fy_medcastles, but i decided the "castles" didn't look like castles at all because i suck at making realistic shapes. 

The dark fort is the T fort, and the light fort is the CT fort. There are two sniper towers in each fort, plus the wall. There are two ladders on the backs of the forts wich can be used for backstabs, because there are two sideways hidden by rocks where you can sneak into the enemy fort without anyone noticing you. 

There is also an underwater tunnel connecting the two forts, 
wich goes trough the river.

I didn't include a NAV file, because it's a pain playing with bots. Why? The T bots pile up on the underwater passage entrance, and the CT bots get stuck in the river.

This is a remake of mp_barn from SOF2 (All rights reserved - copyright Ravensoft). It's my first CS:S map but I think I did a pretty good job and recieved good feedback during play testing.
This map is very dynamic because of the use of physics boxes. One HE nade can shift gameplay significantly as boxes get moved around and/or destroyed. I used a work-around to make bumping the boxes and standing on them work rather well. There are some side-effects to this but they just make things more interesting in my opinion.
It's a relatively small map but supports up to 32 players (I think it rocks one vs one, got up to 8 vs 8 during testing and that was pretty action-packed)
I hope you all enjoy it! Any feedback is appreciated. Also, I'm looking for a good texture artist and modeler to collaborate on other SOF2 remakes with. Drop me a line at phresh@ddkclan.com
